Friendly service, nice atmosphere, and good cocktails. I ordered the Margherita pizza and bruschetta. The bruschetta came assorted fresh mozzarella/tomato/basil, ricotta/pistachios/honey, and whipped goat cheese, mushrooms, aged balsamic.  The Margherita pizza was ok...and the bruschetta would of been better served warm. I liked the ricotta, pistachios, and honey bruschetta the best.

Friendly staff, delicious food! Why only 3 stars?  I was seated at a booth and I was literally the only customer here dining in.  My server opened two huge windows halfway up and let me freeze while I waited for my charcuterie board. The charcuterie board was excellent.  You're allowed to pick anything you wish whether it's cheese, meats and bruschetta or a combination of all three. I was shivering and my hands went numb and asked the staff why the windows needed to be this far open. My server explained that these are the rules they must follow due to covid and other bars and restaurants are being shut down so they are going according to code.  This is literally the first time I've eaten inside a restaurant where the window was left this wide open.  I feel the food itself was delicious and presented well; but the sincere lack of empathy for me was not so attractive. I had half my cheese board boxed up and used it to cook a pasta me for me and my dog later. I completely understand that certain rules are being strictly enforced; but I was freezing by these wide open windows and had a winter moto jacket on! I was the only customer dining here and all the staff were pretty comfortable no where near these windows and running around the restaurant in the heat. For these reasons I am leaving three stars. I don't understand the logic here.

Because of the pandemic we’ve been ordering take out. We always tip 20% but the quality of the food had gotten worse. Just today we ordered pizza and there were only 8 small pieces of pepperoni on the entire pizza. There supposed to be 2 kinds of pepperoni on that pizza but that’s not what we got. I attached the picture. That’s what happened a couple of weeks ago but we thought it was an oversight and that it wouldn’t happen again. Twice within a month when we ordered the Wrightwood salad it came without chicken but because we ordered right before they were closing we couldn’t call and let them know. One time we got the salads without dressing. The other couple of times the salads were visibly smaller than what they should have been. I understand restaurants are hurting but the pandemic shouldn’t justify bad service our poor quality of food especially when most of us leave generous tips. We’ve been patrons of Frasca for 5 years, multiple times per week and I’m so disappointed with their take out service.

It's dependable and the only thing really like it, in the area. Servers are nice and friendly, and it hits that neighborhood feel. Execution of dishes and overall flavor can stand to improve, but it's solid if you're not looking for Michelin stars. I will say it's pricey, even for a Chicago wine bar. The prices are fine, but for a wine bar I feel they can have better wine selections and a more educated staff, on said wine selections. There are no tasting notes on the menu, so knowledge of flavor profile, body, and mouth feel are crucial for venues like these. Having said that, this slight neglect to product knowledge actually pays off, because everywhere else that has a fine wine menu in the city is essentially condescending when they describe wines, even if you're a sommelier. It's always busy, there are some good finds, and if you know how to order and what you're talking about, you can definitely manage an exceptional meal here, for value. I highly recommend!!
